   <section class="page-header-hero wellman-tile" style="background-image: URL('/lib/img/hero/Cal-Day_Panorama1.jpg');">
    <div class="container">
     <div class="caption">
      <div class="caption-inner">
       <h2>
        Telling the Berkeley story
       </h2>
       <div class="caption-body">
        <p>
        </p>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span class="credit">
     Photo by Hulda Nelson
    </span>
   </section>
   <div class="container">
    <div class="inner">
     <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-12">
       <p class="lead">
        If you've ever caught the infectious enthusiasm of a student ambassador leading a campus tour, or felt your chest swell with Berkeley pride after reading about a world-changing faculty research project on
        <em>
         Berkeley News
        </em>
        , you've met the team at the Office of Communications &amp; Public Affairs.
       </p>
       <p>
        As the first point of contact for most visitors—online and offline—we tell the Berkeley story to inspire audiences and elevate the image of the university. We partner closely with various campus audiences—from the chancellor, deans and faculty members, to staff, students and alumni—as well as external media organizations who can amplify Berkeley's important contributions across a wide range of subjects.
       </p>
      </div>
      <!-- / column -->
     </div>
     <!-- / row -->
     <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8">
       <section class="thumb-list">
        <div class="block thumbnail-list-item">
         <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-3">
           <img alt="" src="/lib/img/periodicals.jpg"/>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-9">
           <h2 class="block-header">
            <a href="/news-media-relations.shtml">
             News and Media Relations
            </a>
           </h2>
           <p>
            Staffed by experienced reporters and broadcast journalists, the
            <em>
             Berkeley News
            </em>
            team is your best resource for promoting stories externally or connecting to the right source internally.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="block thumbnail-list-item">
         <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-3">
           <img alt="" src="/lib/img/squirrel.jpg"/>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-9">
           <h2 class="block-header">
            <a href="/brand-marketing-digital-comm.shtml">
             Marketing and Digital Communications
            </a>
           </h2>
           <p>
            The dynamic team that launched a robust brand platform in 2013 and a scalable digital platform in 2015 can help you leverage the Berkeley brand for your marketing initiatives.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="block thumbnail-list-item">
         <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-3">
           <img alt="" src="/lib/img/visit.jpg"/>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-9">
           <h2 class="block-header">
            <a href="/visitor-parent-services.shtml">
             Visitor and Parent Services
            </a>
           </h2>
           <p>
            This core team of hospitality experts manages a number of services for visitors and parents, and is supported by more than 80 student ambassadors. Reach out for tips on welcoming members of your community.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="block thumbnail-list-item">
         <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-3">
           <img alt="" src="/lib/img/bullhorn.jpg"/>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-9">
           <h2 class="block-header">
            <a href="/strategic-communications.shtml">
             Strategic and Critical Communications
            </a>
           </h2>
           <p>
            A team of experienced communicators who manage strategic and critical communications for campus — from executive-level support for campus leadership to crisis communications and issues management for all campus units, to public relations opportunities that coordinate and amplify Berkeley’s mission.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </section>
      </div>
